text: Pushkinskoye () is a rural locality (a village) in Kaltymanovsky Selsoviet, Iglinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 202 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 28 km from Iglino, 10 km from Kaltymanovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Iglinsky District
title: Pushkinskoye, Republic of Bashkortostan
